--------------------------------------------------------------------------

                  Installation instructions for m3di

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Requirements
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
In order to build and install m3di, you will need:
* GNU make (make)
* The GNU C++ compiler (g++) with support for C++14
* The 'jsoncpp' library

Currently, the project relies on a simple Makefile which may require
certain adjustments in case it doesn't work on your system. 

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Installation process
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Navigate to the source directory ./src:
   $ cd src
2. Run make:
   $ make
3. If make finished without errors, install m3di:
   # make install
   On systems with 'sudo' available, you may use
   $ sudo make install
4. If you do not have superuser rights and wish to perform a local 
   install, instead of step 3 you can just copy the binary 'm3di' to
   a directory in your $PATH which you have write access to.

